  "texts": [
    "Hence, we haveη t (ρ H (γ)q) = η t (γ(1)) = (η t • γ)(1) = ρ H (γ)η t (q).Identifying M b ≃ N with an affine map that sends p ∈ M b to e ∈ N, {η t | M b } is identified with a one-parameter family of automorphisms (since it is a one-parameter family of affine maps fixing the identity).",
    "Applying Lemma A.6, we see that ρ H (γ) ∈ Aut(N) for all γ ∈ π 1 (B).",
    "Since the automorphism part of the monodromy is precisely ρ, the claim follows.",
    "□ Proof of Theorem A.",
    "Given a solution (g B, ρ, h) to the twisted harmonic-Einstein equation for the pair (B, G/K), Proposition 3.4 constructs an expanding Ricci soliton (M:= B × ρ N, g, X) satisfying Ansatz 3.1."
